<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/29719674.276531/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTUvbWF0dC1sZXZpbmUtcy1tb25leS1zdHVmZi1iaW5hbmNlLWZ0e=
C1hbmQtY2Fycz9jbXBpZD1CQkQxMTE2MjJfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0=
bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMjExMTYmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R=
1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB562d98bb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> asked yesterday</a> if the=
re has ever been a liquidity crisis at a crypto firm. I didn=E2=80=99t real=
ly get any answers.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But you could imagine how it might go:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A well capitalized conservatively man=
aged crypto lender takes in deposits of crypto and lends them out to other =
crypto trading firms, against good collateral.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-b=
ottom: 5px;">The firm is borrowing short to lend long: Its deposits can be =
recalled on demand, but its loans have longer terms and can=E2=80=99t be re=
called immediately.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Everything is =
fine and great, the loans are performing, the collateral is good.</li>=09<l=
i style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A huge huge huge huge crisis of confidence =
hits the world of centralized crypto firms, for reasons having nothing to d=
o with <em>this</em> good upstanding crypto lender.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">Everyone demands their deposits back, from this lender an=
d from everyone else, due to the crisis of confidence.</li>=09<li style=3D"=
margin-bottom: 5px;">The lender doesn=E2=80=99t have their deposits, becaus=
e it has loaned them to good creditworthy borrowers with good collateral an=
d can=E2=80=99t get them back immediately.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In this scenario, the lender is perfectly solv=
ent =E2=80=94=C2=A0the money is safe and will be paid back in full, reasona=
bly soon, leaving more than enough to repay depositors =E2=80=94=C2=A0but i=
lliquid. It is a classic normal bank run.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Is that this? Man, <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29719674.276531/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnL=
mNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTYvY3J5cHRvLWJyb2tlcmFnZS1nZW5lc2lzLXN1=
c3BlbmRzLXdpdGhkcmF3YWxzLWFuZC1vcmlnaW5hdGlvbnMtYXQtbGVuZGluZy1hcm0_Y21waWQ=
9QkJEMTExNjIyX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZX=
R0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjIxMTE2JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB09ec06eb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;"> what do I know</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The fallout from the collapse of Sam Bankman-F=
ried=E2=80=99s sprawling crypto empire spread Wednesday, with digital-asset=
 brokerage Genesis and crypto exchange Gemini becoming the latest pain poin=
ts.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Genesis is suspending redemptions and new loan=
 originations at its lending business after facing what it described as =E2=
=80=9Cabnormal withdrawal requests.=E2=80=9D Gemini, founded by Cameron Win=
klevoss and Tyler Winklevoss, subsequently announced its yield product targ=
eting retail investors will also halt redemptions as Genesis was a key part=
ner in the program.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As a counterparty to many in the sector, Genes=
is=E2=80=99 financial health has been closely watched as a gauge of the ind=
ustry=E2=80=99s strength or for signs of potential contagion. Some of Genes=
is=E2=80=99 biggest lenders include crypto exchange Gemini, which offers a =
product to users to generate yield through Genesis, according to its websit=
e. On Wednesday, Gemini announced that it=E2=80=99s working with Genesis to=
 help customers redeem their funds from the Earn product =E2=80=9Cas quickl=
y as possible.=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Genesis=E2=80=99s withdrawal requests exceeded=
 current liquidity at Genesis Global Capital, the lending arm, according to=
 interim Chief Executive Officer Derar Islim. The New York-based company ha=
s hired advisers to explore all possible options, including raising new fun=
ding, and will deliver a plan for its lending business next week, Islim sai=
d. Alvarez &amp; Marsal and the law firm Cleary Gottlieb are advising Genes=
is.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We talked yesterday about Binance Holdings Ltd=
.=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/297196=
74.276531/aHR0cHM6Ly90d2l0dGVyLmNvbS9jel9iaW5hbmNlL3N0YXR1cy8xNTkyMDQ0NDk2M=
Tc0NjEyNDgy/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcf9d8c72" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" items=
cope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decorati=
on: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000=
; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> proposal</a> for a =
sort of central bank of crypto, an =E2=80=9Cindustry recovery fund=E2=80=9D=
 that would =E2=80=9Chelp projects who are otherwise strong, but in a liqui=
dity crisis.=E2=80=9D The sudden collapse of Sam Bankman-Fried=E2=80=99s cr=
ypto exchange FTX.com, and his associated crypto hedge fund Alameda Researc=
h,=C2=A0<em>could=C2=A0</em>trigger liquidity crises at otherwise healthy c=
rypto firms. Or, of course, not. Those firms could have had assets at FTX t=
hat are now gone. Or they could have made undercollateralized loans to Alam=
eda that are now gone. What do I know. In any case the FTX collapse trigger=
ed a crisis of confidence that spread to other firms, healthy or not.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One solution to this problem is that the centr=
al bank of crypto could sort it out: Firms that run into trouble could go t=
o Binance, and Binance could examine their books and decide if they=E2=80=
=99re solvent, and if they are then the industry recovery fund could lend t=
hem the money to keep their doors open. It <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/29719674.276531/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucmV1dGVycy5jb20vdG=
VjaG5vbG9neS9iaW5hbmNlLWNlby16aGFvLXNpZ25pZmljYW50LWludGVyZXN0LWNyeXB0by1pb=
mR1c3RyeS1yZWNvdmVyeS1mdW5kLTIwMjItMTEtMTYv/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB3771a4=
95" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> seems to be moving forward</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Binance Chief Executive Changpeng Zhao said on=
 Wednesday there was significant interest from industry players in a recove=
ry fund his company plans to launch to help crypto projects facing a liquid=
ity squeeze following the collapse of rival FTX.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Speaking at a conference in Abu Dhabi, Zhao sa=
id he doesn't have an exact figure in mind for the size of the recovery fun=
d.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"There are players that have strong financials=
 and we should band together; we've got significant interest so far," he sa=
id, declining to name other exchanges or institutions at this point.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But isn=E2=80=99t that a weird solution, for c=
rypto? That some fund run by the biggest exchange would examine each firm=
=E2=80=99s secret balance sheets and decide who is worthy of a bailout? Wha=
t if =E2=80=A6=C2=A0what if there was some sort of=C2=A0<em>decentralized=
=C2=A0</em>solution? For instance, what if crypto firms made their balance =
sheets=C2=A0<em>public</em>, perhaps with some sort of auditing from a neut=
ral expert=C2=A0accountant, so that investors could decide for themselves w=
hich firms were solvent and which were in trouble?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Oh I am kidding, a little. Of course my point =
is that this is how normal public companies in traditional finance=C2=A0=E2=
=80=94=C2=A0including big banks =E2=80=94=C2=A0work. But it is not like the=
 published audited quarterly balance sheets of big public=C2=A0traditional =
financial institutions actually tell you all=C2=A0<em>that=C2=A0</em>much a=
bout their financial health, in a crisis; they are mostly too complicated a=
nd too delayed to provide definitive answers to questions like =E2=80=9Cdid=
 this bank run out of money an hour ago?=E2=80=9D But they help. The actual=
 method that traditional finance has hit upon for addressing these problems=
 is a complex combination of (1) public financial disclosure, (2) safety-an=
d-soundness regulation to keep banks from taking too many dumb risks, (3) c=
apital and liquidity regulation to make sure they have enough money, (4) ce=
ntral bank liquidity support, (5) deposit insurance for customers, etc.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Even=C2=A0before last week=E2=80=99s FTX meltd=
own, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/29719674.2765=
31/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9mZWF0dXJlcy8yMDIyLXRoZS1jcnlwdG8tc3Rv=
cnkvP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMTYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJ=
jZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTExNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8796f494" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  I liked to say</a>=C2=A0that the =
crypto industry managed to reinvent the 2008 financial crisis, complete wit=
h opaque leverage and financial contagion. And for ages I have been saying =
that crypto is in the business of re-learning all the lessons of traditiona=
l finance. This week, it is learning the lesson of =E2=80=9Cit is good to h=
ave a central bank.=E2=80=9D But I am not sure that=E2=80=99s the=C2=A0<em>=
best=C2=A0</em>lesson to learn here? And it is certainly not the=C2=A0<em>o=
nly=C2=A0</em>one.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/29719674.276531/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMTUvZnR4LXMtY3J5cHRvLWNvbnRhZ2lvbi1pbmZlY3RzLWZpcm1zLWZyb20=
tYmxvY2tmaS10by12b3lhZ2VyP2NtcGlkPUJCRDExMTYyMl9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW=
09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIyMTExNiZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ=
249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1e34c0dc" itemprop=3D"StoryLink"=
 itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-de=
coration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #=
000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Elsewhere</a>=
:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlockFi, which said in a Monday blog post that=
 it had =E2=80=9Csignificant exposure=E2=80=9D to FTX and the company=E2=80=
=99s related entities, is preparing a potential bankruptcy filing, the Wall=
 Street Journal reported. BlockFi halted withdrawals last week over uncerta=
inties about FTX.=C2=A0 =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Bankrupt crypto lender Voyager was forced to t=
ry to find a replacement buyer for its assets after concluding FTX wouldn=
=E2=80=99t close a planned $1.4 billion deal to buy the company.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t think we=E2=80=99ve s=
een the end of the contagion factor or the fear that is running through the=
 market,=E2=80=9D Voyager=E2=80=99s main bankruptcy attorney Joshua Sussber=
g said during a court hearing Tuesday.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">BlockFi and Voyager are both examples of troub=
led crypto firms that got bailouts from the central bank of crypto, back th=
is summer when that central bank=C2=A0<em>was FTX. </em>Trusting one guy to=
 save the crypto financial system in crisis introduces its own, pretty obvi=
ous risks.</p>
